<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1436,1751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maskell" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,325,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patella">
<emphasis box="[151,325,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Inglisia patella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[574,729,1436,1463]" name="New Zealand" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, and was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C." box="[1025,1377,1436,1463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" refId="ref11515" refString="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. (2000) Coccidae (Insecta: Hemiptera: Coccoidea). Manaaki Whenua Press, Lincoln, Canterbury, 259 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hodgson &amp; Henderson (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. It is unlike any other known soft scale and it is clear that none of the other seven species currently included in the genus are congeneric with it. Here the three African species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hall, 1935" authorityName="Hall" authorityYear="1935" box="[772,1034,1508,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grevilliae">
<emphasis box="[772,903,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">I. grevilliae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hall, W. J." box="[912,1034,1508,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="73 - 84" refId="ref11180" refString="Hall, W. J. (1935) Observations on the Coccidae of southern Rhodesia - VI. Stylops, 4, 73 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1935. tb 00561. x" type="journal article" year="1935">Hall, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hodgson, 1967 b" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" box="[1047,1363,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluvialis">
<emphasis box="[1047,1167,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">I. pluvialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[1176,1363,1508,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11311" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1967 b) A revision of the species of Inglisia Maskell (Homoptera: Coccoidea) recorded from the Ethiopian region. Arnoldia, Rhodesia, 3 (23), 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1967">Hodgson, 1967b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Newstead, 1917" authorityName="Newstead" authorityYear="1917" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">I. theobromae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Newstead, R." box="[294,477,1544,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref11922" refString="Newstead, R. (1917) Observations on scale-insects (Coccidae) - IV. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 8, 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300036476" type="journal article" year="1917">Newstead, 1917</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell, 1900" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1900" box="[694,1033,1544,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Cryptinglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[694,842,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Cryptinglisia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell, T. D. A." box="[852,1033,1544,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="173 - 174" refId="ref10853" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1900) A new genus of Coccidae injuring the roots of the grapevine in South Africa. The Entomologist, 33, 173 - 174." type="journal article" year="1900">Cockerell, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hall)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1076,1295,1544,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grevilliae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1076,1218,1544,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. grevilliae</emphasis>
(Hall)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1305,1436,1545,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1305,1436,1545,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,229,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,189,1966]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1974]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cryptinglisia. grevilliae (Hall). Adult female. After Hodgson 1967b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222979/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hodgson)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" box="[254,515,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluvialis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[254,385,1580,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. pluvialis</emphasis>
(Hodgson)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[524,656,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[524,650,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[674,744,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1991,2015]" captionTargetBox="[238,1349,192,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[238,1349,181,1967]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cryptinglisia pluvialis (Hodgson). Adult female. After Hodgson 1967b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222983/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Newstead)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Newstead" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[811,1118,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[811,979,1580,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. theobromae</emphasis>
(Newstead)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1127,1257,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1127,1257,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1275,1346,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1916,1940]" captionTargetBox="[163,1434,192,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,181,1892]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cryptinglisia theobromae (Newstead). Adult female. After Hodgson 1967b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222989/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). A full description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" box="[315,445,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluvialis">
<emphasis box="[315,445,1616,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. pluvialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[586,772,1616,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref11353" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1969) Notes on Rhodesian Coccidae (Homoptera: Coccoidea): Part III. Arnoldia, Rhodesia, 4, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1969">Hodgson (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[855,995,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grevilliae">
<emphasis box="[855,995,1616,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. grevilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Newstead" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[1051,1218,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis box="[1051,1218,1616,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. theobromae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are fully described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[180,380,1652,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11311" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1967 b) A revision of the species of Inglisia Maskell (Homoptera: Coccoidea) recorded from the Ethiopian region. Arnoldia, Rhodesia, 3 (23), 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1967">Hodgson (1967b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1436,1751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
It would appear that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1900" box="[431,579,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Cryptinglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,579,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Cryptinglisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two centres of population, Central and South America and 
<collectingCountry box="[1287,1433,1688,1714]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. There do not appear to be any clear morphological characters separating these 11 species into subgroups.
</paragraph>
